d with any translation, giving readers in-depth access to the Sanskrit text.This book is designed for those with little or no knowledge of Sanskrit as well as those familiar with the original text. It allows readers to gain a greater reach into the Bhagavad Gītā and achieve a deeper understanding of its ideas, facilitating nuanced analyses of the text and its language. It is an essential reference for scholars, teachers, students, and other readers interested in India’s spiritual classics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBhagavadgītā-Concordances. 0aLexicography. 7aRELIGION / Hinduism / Sacred Writings.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311074968740uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/schw1413240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231559409423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231559409/original  a978-3-11-074968-7  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles